This article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 11, 2014, as the International Day of the Girl. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of providing girls and women with equal opportunities to learn, grow, and achieve their full potential. It highlights the various challenges faced by girls and women globally, such as gender-based violence, harmful cultural norms, and barriers to education and healthcare. The proclamation discusses the efforts of the Obama Administration to promote gender equality and uplift the status of girls and women, both domestically and internationally. It mentions initiatives aimed at addressing issues like teen dating violence, sexual assault, domestic violence, human trafficking, and barriers to healthcare. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe the International Day of the Girl and engage in activities that advance equality and opportunities for girls worldwide.